description.narrative: To respond to the low accessibility of the disability grant for CwDs, an assessment on policy and implementation of the grant was conducted in partnership with TU, key findings were discussed with DEPD and recommendations put in place with strong commitment from the DEPD to propose key recommendations to the National Committee on Disabilities. To ensure that children under 6 will receive the CSG in time, UNICEF TCO supported the RTG to strengthen the Management Information System (MIS), improving communication at all levels, and finalize the internal monitoring framework and indicators. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019

Extent to which the CSG is effectively monitored Level 1: Assessment of the CSG monitoring system completed and draft revisions in place Level 2: Policy and operational guidelines revised to accommodate adjustments suggested by the assessment Level 3: MSDHS/PSD and MOI/TAO staff trained to implemented policy adjustments Level 4: Information from the CSG monitoring system has been analyzed and reported in the previous year
